-- Mexico Stocks: Elektra, Mexichem, OHL Mexico Were Active
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   L a y a
-- 2012-07-13T21:59:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/mexico-stocks-elektra-mexichem-ohl-mexico-were-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico City trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index rose 0.6 percent to 40,498.47.  Grupo Elektra SAB (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , rose 2.5
percent to 556.73 pesos.  Bolsa Mexicana de Valores SAB , the
operator of Mexico’s stock exchange, said a proposed change that
could result in Grupo Elektra SAB being removed from the
benchmark IPC index is still blocked by a lawsuit from the
company.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM*)   rose 1.4 percent to 58.62 pesos.
Mexichem, Latin America’s biggest maker of plastic pipes, said
its sewer pipe maker in the Netherlands, Wavin NV, renegotiated
bank debt.  OHL Mexico SAB (OHLMEX*)   rose 3.3 percent to 18.05
pesos. The company’s shares were punished excessively by the
lost of a concession in Puebla earlier this year and does not
reflect the potential of other active projects with the
government, according to a note published by Grupo Financiero Ve
Por Mas SA. Their target price for the end of the year is 20.4
pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Laya in  New York  at 
